{
  "texts": [
    "That ultimately leads to the identification of relevant components.",
    "ML algorithms or Classifiers process these features selected for analysis.",
    "The feature engineering method consists of two segments: the first aims to extract parts from an existing image dataset, and the second involves picking features among the extracted ones.",
    "Methods like Gabor, Zernike, Haralick, and Tamura were used to extract features [110].",
    "Features may be selected using techniques like the gray level co-occurrence matrices (GLCM), local binary pattern (LBP), and CNN."
  ]
}